# GSRC AI Initiatives Repository — Development Plan 2.0

Tech Stack: Python (FastAPI) + React (Ant Design via CDN) + SQLite
Status: All 6 phases implemented and working
Last Updated: March 27, 2026

---

## Phase 1: Project Foundation & Data Layer

- FastAPI backend with CORS, error handling
- SQLAlchemy models for Case Library schema:
  - Case ID (UUID, auto), Owner Login, Job Level, Program/Team
  - Use Case Title, Problem Statement, Solution Description
  - AI Technique, Platform, Dev Type, Is Chatbot
  - Tools/Services, Key Prompts, Impact Expected (output_outcome)
  - Time Saved %, Yearly HC Saved, Accuracy %, Cost Reduction %, Yearly USD Saved
  - Dev Time Hours, Status, Scalability Score, Innovation Score
  - Date Created (auto), Date Updated (auto), Rank
- CRUD API: POST/GET/PUT/DELETE /cases
- SQLite database with seed data (5 sample cases)
- GET /cases/options — dropdown values served from constants.py

---

## Phase 2: Learner Input Portal & User Auth

### Submission Form (Modal Popup)
- "New Initiative" button on Browse page opens modal form
- Sectioned layout: Basic Information → Project Details → Impact & Benefits
- Dropdowns for all categorical fields (see constants below)
- Radio buttons for Is Chatbot (Yes/No)
- Sliders for Scalability Score and Innovation Score (1-10)
- Numeric fields auto-converted (string → float) before API call
- Empty fields stripped from payload to avoid validation errors
- Owner auto-populated from logged-in user (not editable)

### User Authentication
- User model: login, email, display_name, hashed_password, role (learner/admin)
- JWT token auth with 8-hour expiry
- Register, Login, Forgot Password, Reset Password flows
- Password reset via token (printed to server console for hackathon)
- Role-based access: learners edit own cases, admins edit all
- React hooks ordering fix: all useState before conditional returns

### Admin User Management
- Admin dropdown menu → "Manage Users" modal
- List all users with login, name, email, role
- Change role inline (learner ↔ admin dropdown)
- Delete users (default admin protected)
- Add new users with inline form
- Backend: GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /admin/users (admin only)

### Dropdown Constants
- JOB_LEVELS: L3, L4, L5, L6, L7, L8
- PROGRAMS_TEAMS: Chemical Safety, Climate Pledge Friendly, Dangerous Goods, Environmental Assurance and Protection, EU Deforestation Regulation, Food Safety Operations, Global Trade Services, North American Customer Fulfillment, ONT, Private Brands, Quality Operations, Support Function, Sustainability, Transport Risk Compliance, Others
- AI_TECHNIQUES: NLP Text Classification, Time Series Forecasting, Generative AI (LLM), Computer Vision, Reinforcement Learning, Anomaly Detection, Recommendation Systems, Others
- PLATFORMS: PartyRock, Quick Suite, AgentZ, Bedrock, Custom, Other
- DEV_TYPES: No code, Low code, High Code
- IS_CHATBOT: Yes, No
- STATUSES: Developing, UAT, In Production

---

## Phase 3: Filterable Browse UI

### Card View (3 per row)
- Initiative cards with tags for Platform, Dev Type, Chatbot, Status
- Click title → read-only detail modal (all users)
- Edit/Delete buttons only for owners and admins

### Quick Filters
- Dedicated filter states: Status, Platform, Chatbot (independent toggles)
- "All" button and "✕ Clear" to reset all filters
- Global text search across title, owner, program, technique, problem
- CSV export button: GET /cases/export

### Detail View Modal (all users)
- Opens on initiative name click
- Shows: title, owner, program, status, technique, platform, dev type, chatbot
- Three highlighted sections: Problem Statement, Solution Description, Impact Expected
- Metrics row: Time Saved, HC/yr, Accuracy, USD/yr, Dev Hours, Cost Reduction
- Edit button in footer (only for owners/admins)

---

## Phase 4: Analytics Dashboard

### Summary Cards (6 cards)
- Total Initiatives, Avg Time Saved, HC Saved/yr, USD Saved/yr, Total Dev Hours, Avg Accuracy

### Charts (pure CSS/React, no external dependency)
1. Platform Distribution — bar chart
2. Status Distribution — color-coded bars
3. AI Technique — donut chart
4. Development Type — donut chart (green/orange/red)
5. Chatbot Analysis — donut chart (cyan/gray)
6. USD Saved by Program — horizontal bars
7. Submissions Timeline — vertical bar chart

### Data Table (bottom of dashboard)
- All cases with all fields displayed
- Custom filter dropdowns with "Select All" checkbox
- Filterable: Owner, Program, Technique, Platform, Dev Type, Chatbot, Status
- Sortable: all numeric columns
- High-contrast dark theme filter UI

### Backend Endpoints
- GET /analytics/summary, by-program, by-technique, by-status, trends
- GET /analytics/by-platform, by-dev-type, by-chatbot

---

## Phase 5: Ranking Engine + AI Analysis

### Part A: Weighted Scoring & Leaderboard (Admin Only)
- Composite score = weighted sum of normalized metrics (0-100)
- 4 weight sliders with total % indicator (must equal 100%)
- Refresh button (disabled until total = 100%)
- Top 3 highlighted with medal icons
- GET /rankings with configurable weight params

### Part B: Rule-Based AI Analysis
- "AI Analysis" button on each leaderboard row
- Compares case metrics against library averages
- Generates: Strengths, Weaknesses, Suggestions, Risks
- Modal popup with structured analysis sections
- POST /rankings/{case_id}/ai-analysis

---

## Phase 6: AI Solution Design Agent

### Keyword-Based Similarity Matching
- Tokenize query, score against all cases with field weighting
- Returns top matching cases with similarity scores

### Solution Design Generation
- Recommended technique, tools, effort estimate
- Technique-specific implementation steps (10 steps)
- Reference cases from library

### Chat Interface
- Chat-style UI in dedicated tab
- First message → full solution design card
- Follow-up → contextual answers (cost, scaling, timeline, risk, team)
- Session-based conversation tracking
- POST /agent/design, POST /agent/followup

---

