## Deployment Options

### Option A: Local Only
```
py -m uvicorn app.main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
```

### Option B: Corp Network (from laptop)
```
py -m uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080
```
Note: Use port 8080 to avoid AWS WorkDocs conflict on 8000.

### Option C: EC2 (t3.small, ~$16/month)
See detailed steps below.

---

## EC2 Deployment Plan

### Step 1: Launch EC2
- AMI: Amazon Linux 2023, Type: t3.small
- Security group: SSH (22) from your IP, HTTP (80) from 10.0.0.0/8
- Storage: 8 GB gp3

### Step 2: Install
```bash
ssh -i key.pem ec2-user@<private-ip>
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install -y python3.11 python3.11-pip git
```

### Step 3: Deploy
```bash
git clone https://github.com/bjwolf/ai-case-library.git
cd ai-case-library/backend
python3.11 -m pip install -r requirements.txt
python3.11 seed_data.py
```

### Step 4: Systemd Service
```bash
sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/ai-case-library.service << 'EOF'
[Unit]
Description=AI Case Library
After=network.target
[Service]
User=ec2-user
WorkingDirectory=/home/ec2-user/ai-case-library/backend
ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3.11 -m uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 80
Restart=always
[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
EOF
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable ai-case-library
sudo systemctl start ai-case-library
```

### Step 5: Access
Anyone on Amazon VPN: http://<instance-private-ip>/

### Optional: Route 53 DNS
Create Private Hosted Zone → A record → ai-case-library.gsrc.internal → EC2 private IP

### Cost: ~$16/month (24/7) or ~$5/month (business hours only)

