## Canopy Deployment (Recommended)

### Overview
Canopy is Amazon's internal app hosting platform on ECS Fargate with built-in Midway auth, persistent S3 storage, and Bedrock LLM access. Zero infrastructure management.

### Canopy Version Structure
```
canopy/
├── app.py              ← FastAPI entry point (port 8080, host 0.0.0.0)
├── requirements.txt    ← fastapi, uvicorn, jinja2, boto3, pydantic
├── constants.py        ← All dropdown options (7 lists)
├── seed_data.py        ← Sample data (auto-seeds on first startup)
├── ranking.py          ← Scoring engine + AI analysis
├── agent.py            ← Solution design agent (Bedrock or keyword fallback)
└── templates/
    ├── base.html       ← Dark sci-fi layout (all CSS inline, zero CDN)
    ├── browse.html     ← Card view + filters + form/detail modals
    ├── dashboard.html  ← Stats + charts + data table
    ├── leaderboard.html← Rankings + weight sliders + AI analysis
    └── agent.html      ← Chat interface
```

### Key Differences from Local Version
| Aspect | Local (backend/) | Canopy (canopy/) |
|---|---|---|
| Database | SQLite + SQLAlchemy | canopy_storage (S3 JSON) |
| Auth | Custom JWT + login page | Midway SSO (automatic) |
| Frontend | React + Ant Design (CDN) | Jinja2 + vanilla JS (no CDN) |
| AI Agent | Keyword matching | Bedrock Claude (with fallback) |
| AI Analysis | Rule-based | Bedrock Claude (with fallback) |
| Port | 8000 | 8080 |
| Entry point | backend/app/main.py | canopy/app.py |
| Dependencies | 8 packages | 6 packages |

### Canopy SDK (auto-injected, not bundled)
- canopy_storage — persistent S3-backed key/value storage
- canopy_llm — Amazon Bedrock Claude for AI features
- canopy_auth — Midway user identity from headers
- canopy_email — SES email sending
- canopy_scheduler — background jobs
- canopy_cache — in-memory caching with TTL

### Local Testing
```bash
cd "AI Hackathon/canopy"
set CANOPY_DEV_USER=guoweim
py app.py
# Opens on http://localhost:8080
```

### Deploy to Canopy
```powershell
cd "AI Hackathon/canopy"
Compress-Archive -Path app.py, requirements.txt, constants.py, ranking.py, agent.py, seed_data.py, templates -DestinationPath canopy-deploy.zip
```
Upload ZIP to https://canopy.fgbs.amazon.dev

### Access
Any Amazon employee globally: https://canopy.fgbs.amazon.dev/apps/gsrc-ai-initiatives/
Midway authenticates automatically — no login page needed.

### Admin Bootstrap
- DEFAULT_ADMINS = ["guoweim"] hardcoded in app.py
- First visit auto-creates roles in canopy_storage
- Admin can promote others via User Management UI

### Git Branch
- `main` branch: local version (React + SQLite)
- `canopy` branch: Canopy version (Jinja2 + canopy_storage)
